##
## Cantilever beam bending, UP (u-p) formulation, Updated Lagrangian (UPDATELAG)
##   Mesh: 5x1x1 hex (beam_up_ul.msh), L=5, b=h=1
##   Material: E=1000, nu=0.499999 (nearly incompressible), !ELASTIC,CAUCHY -> UPDATELAG
##   Load: tip force -1.0 at SET_4 (2 nodes), fixed end SET_1, NLSTATIC 10 substeps
##
## Purpose:
##   Verify the UPDATELAG branch of the UP element. Same model/load as the
##   TOTALLAG case (beam_up.cnt); the final-step tip deflection must be close
##   to it (uy_UL = -1.4095 vs uy_TL = -1.4139, ~0.3% diff), confirming the
##   two formulations give a consistent solution. Newton converges in 5-6 iters.
##
!VERSION
 3
!SOLUTION, TYPE=NLSTATIC
!WRITE,LOG
!WRITE,RESULT
## CG solves the displacement-only system (element-level static condensation of
## the pressure DOF -> SPD). nu=0.499999 penalty conditioning limits the relative
## residual to ~6e-5, so the tolerance is 1e-4 (matches the direct solver to ~1e-7).
!SOLVER,METHOD=CG,PRECOND=1,NSET=0,ITERLOG=NO,TIMELOG=NO
 10000, 1
 1.0e-04, 1.00, 0.0
!BOUNDARY, GRPID=1
 SET_1,1,1
 SET_1,2,2
 SET_1,3,3
!CLOAD, GRPID=1
 SET_4,2,-1.0
!MATERIAL, NAME=MATERIAL1
!ELASTIC, CAUCHY
 1.0000E+03, 4.99999E-01
!SECTION, SECNUM=1, FORM361=UP
!STEP, SUBSTEPS=10, CONVERG=1.0E-06
 BOUNDARY,1
 LOAD,1
!END
